@startuml
title Credential Guard — secret access under VBS isolation

participant "Application" as APP
participant "LSA\n(VTL0, normal world)" as LSA
participant "LSAIso\n(VTL1, secure world)" as LSAISO
participant "Remote service" as SVC

APP -> LSA : authenticate (needs a credential)
LSA -> LSAISO : RPC: "use the secret"
note over LSAISO
  Hash / Kerberos key never
  leaves VTL1. The hypervisor
  enforces the VTL0 / VTL1 boundary.
end note
LSAISO -> LSAISO : compute response / derive key\nusing the protected secret
LSAISO --> LSA : opaque result (no secret)
LSA -> SVC : authenticate with result
SVC --> LSA : access granted
note over LSA, SVC
  An attacker dumping LSASS in VTL0
  finds no reusable hash or ticket.
end note
@enduml
